<FlowDocument xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml/presentation"
              xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2006/xaml"
              Foreground="#E0E0E0"
              Background="#1E1F22"
              FontFamily="Segoe UI"
              FontSize="14"
              PagePadding="32,24,32,24">

    <Paragraph FontSize="28" FontWeight="Bold" Foreground="#FFD700" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Cone Penalties Event Point
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Foreground="#A0A0A0" FontSize="13" Margin="0,0,0,16">
        Adds time penalties when traffic cones are hit, but only when used with a Count Up timer and traffic cone Create Barrel Event Points.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,0,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- OVERVIEW -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,4,0,4">
        What Cone Penalties Does
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The <Bold>Cone Penalties</Bold> Event Point is a very small but very specific support Event
        Point. Its purpose is to increase a timer upward when traffic cones are hit.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Cone Penalties does not create cones, does not create a timer, and does not have its own
        type-specific settings. It only becomes useful when the correct supporting Event Points also
        exist in the mission.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_cone_penalties_overview.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#4A2424" BorderBrush="#C45A5A" BorderThickness="2"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="14">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#FFD0D0" FontSize="15">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Critical dependency:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Cone Penalties only has an effect if a Count Up timer Event Point also exists.
                    It is not a standalone penalty system.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- REQUIRED SUPPORTING EVENT POINTS -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Required Supporting Event Points
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Cone Penalties depends on other Event Points. A working cone penalty setup normally requires
        all of the following pieces:
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                A <Bold>Count Up</Bold> timer Event Point. This is the timer that can be increased.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                One or more <Bold>Create Barrel</Bold> Event Points configured as <Bold>Traffic Cones</Bold>.
                These are the cones the player can hit.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
        <ListItem>
            <Paragraph>
                A <Bold>Cone Penalties</Bold> Event Point. This enables the penalty behaviour that
                adds time when cone transgressions occur.
            </Paragraph>
        </ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        If the cones exist but there is no Count Up timer, the Cone Penalties Event Point has
        nothing useful to increase. If the Count Up timer exists but there are no traffic cone Event
        Points, there are no cone hits to penalise. If both exist but Cone Penalties is missing, the
        cone hits will not apply the intended time penalty behaviour.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_cone_penalties_required_setup.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A2F3A" BorderBrush="#4A5A7A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#AFC8FF">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Think of the three parts like this:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Count Up is the timer. Create Barrel / Traffic Cone is the thing the player can hit.
                    Cone Penalties is the rule that says hitting those cones adds penalty time.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- TYPE SPECIFIC PROPERTIES -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Type-Specific Properties
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Cone Penalties has <Bold>no type-specific properties</Bold>. There is no item type, cone
        type, count value, penalty value, radius value, or target field to configure directly on the
        Cone Penalties Event Point itself.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Its behaviour comes from its presence in the mission and the existence of the correct
        supporting Event Points. The actual cones are created separately using <Bold>Create Barrel</Bold>
        Event Points set to Traffic Cone. The timer is created separately using a <Bold>Count Up</Bold>
        timer Event Point.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_cone_penalties_edit_window.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- COMMON PROPERTIES -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Common Properties
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Cone Penalties still has the normal Event Point common properties, such as index number,
        Event Point type, letter group, colour, position, trigger settings, and listening mode.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Because Cone Penalties is more of a mission rule or support Event Point, its map position is
        usually not as important as the placement of the traffic cones or timer logic. You can still
        place it somewhere sensible for organisation, such as near the Count Up timer Event Point or
        near the cone challenge area.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_cone_penalties_common_properties.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- HOW THE SYSTEM WORKS -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        How Cone Penalties Works
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The intended setup is a time challenge where the player is racing against a timer. A
        <Bold>Count Up</Bold> timer is present, and traffic cones are placed as obstacles using
        <Bold>Create Barrel</Bold> Event Points set to Traffic Cone.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        When the player hits a traffic cone, that cone hit is treated as a transgression. If the
        Cone Penalties Event Point is present and the Count Up timer exists, the timer is increased
        upward, effectively adding a time penalty.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Border Background="#25272B" BorderBrush="#444" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="10">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#E0E0E0" FontFamily="Consolas">
Count Up timer exists + Traffic Cone is hit + Cone Penalties exists = Timer increases
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph>
        In practical terms, Cone Penalties is a modifier for a cone-driving or cone-avoidance
        challenge. It is not something most missions need unless they specifically include a timed
        section where hitting cones should punish the player.
    </Paragraph>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- CREATE BARREL / TRAFFIC CONES -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Traffic Cones Are Created Separately
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Cone Penalties does not create the cones. The cones are separate Event Points.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        To create cones, use the <Bold>Create Barrel</Bold> Event Point and set its type to
        <Bold>Traffic Cone</Bold>. Each cone is its own Create Barrel Event Point. If you need ten
        cones, place ten Create Barrel / Traffic Cone Event Points or copy and paste them.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_cone_penalties_traffic_cones.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#3A2A2A" BorderBrush="#7A4A4A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#E0A0A0">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Important:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Cone Penalties only applies to traffic cone-style transgressions. Do not expect it to work with ordinary barrels,
                    bins, burning barrels, or unrelated objects unless that behaviour has been specifically tested.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- COUNT UP TIMER -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Count Up Timer Requirement
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        The Count Up timer is the timer that receives the penalty. Without a Count Up timer Event
        Point, Cone Penalties has no useful timer to increase.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        Use a Count Up timer when you want the player’s completion time or penalty time to increase
        as mistakes happen. Cone Penalties then adds time to that timer whenever a valid traffic cone
        transgression occurs.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_cone_penalties_count_up_timer.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- TRIGGER SETTINGS -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Trigger Settings
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        Cone Penalties is usually configured so that it exists while the timed challenge is active.
        The exact trigger depends on how your mission starts and stops the cone challenge.
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        For a simple always-available setup, you can make it active from the start of the mission:
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Triggered By:</Bold> None / Game Starts.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph><Bold>Listening Mode:</Bold> Active.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph Margin="0,6,0,0">
        For a more controlled setup, place Cone Penalties behind the same mission logic that starts
        the timed cone challenge. For example, it could activate only after a race starts, a switch
        is used, a conversation finishes, or a dependency Event Point fires.
    </Paragraph>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_cone_penalties_trigger_settings.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- EXAMPLE -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Example: Timed Cone Challenge
    </Paragraph>
    <Paragraph>
        A typical use case is a driving or movement challenge where the player must complete a route
        without hitting traffic cones. Each cone hit adds penalty time.
    </Paragraph>

    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create a <Bold>Count Up</Bold> timer Event Point for the challenge timer.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create several <Bold>Create Barrel</Bold> Event Points and set them to <Bold>Traffic Cone</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Place the traffic cones along the route or around the challenge area.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create a <Bold>Cone Penalties</Bold> Event Point.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Trigger Cone Penalties when the challenge is active, or set it to exist from the start if the challenge is always active.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Save and test the mission.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Hit a cone during the test and confirm the Count Up timer increases.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,6,0,8">
        <Image Source="pack://application:,,,/UrbanChaosMissionEditor;component/Help/Images/mission_cone_penalties_example_route.png"
               MaxWidth="720" Stretch="Uniform"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- TROUBLESHOOTING -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <BlockUIContainer>
        <Border Height="1" Background="#444" Margin="0,14,0,12"/>
    </BlockUIContainer>

    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,0,0,4">
        Troubleshooting
    </Paragraph>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Hitting cones does not add time</Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="32,0,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm a <Bold>Count Up</Bold> timer Event Point exists.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm a <Bold>Cone Penalties</Bold> Event Point exists.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the cones are actually <Bold>Create Barrel</Bold> Event Points set to <Bold>Traffic Cone</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm Cone Penalties is active while the challenge is running.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Confirm the timer being inspected is the Count Up timer expected to receive the penalty.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">The timer exists but never changes</Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="32,0,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Check whether the Count Up timer is active.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Check whether the challenge logic is starting the timer correctly.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Check whether the Cone Penalties Event Point is triggered or active.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <Paragraph FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#E8B84B" Margin="8,8,0,1">Objects are hit but no penalty is applied</Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Disc" Margin="32,0,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Make sure the objects are traffic cones, not ordinary barrels, bins, burning barrels, or other props.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Use the Create Barrel Event Point type that specifically creates traffic cones.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <!-- BASIC WORKFLOW -->
    <!-- ============================================================ -->
    <Paragraph FontSize="22" FontWeight="SemiBold" Foreground="#7AD7FF" Margin="0,12,0,4">
        Basic Cone Penalties Workflow
    </Paragraph>
    <List MarkerStyle="Decimal" Margin="16,2,0,0">
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create the <Bold>Count Up</Bold> timer Event Point.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create one or more <Bold>Create Barrel</Bold> Event Points set to <Bold>Traffic Cone</Bold>.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Place the traffic cones where the player can hit or avoid them.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Create the <Bold>Cone Penalties</Bold> Event Point.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Make Cone Penalties active while the cone challenge is running.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Save and test the mission.</Paragraph></ListItem>
        <ListItem><Paragraph>Hit a cone and confirm the Count Up timer increases.</Paragraph></ListItem>
    </List>

    <BlockUIContainer Margin="0,8,0,8">
        <Border Background="#2A3A2A" BorderBrush="#4A7A4A" BorderThickness="1"
                CornerRadius="4" Padding="12">
            <TextBlock TextWrapping="Wrap" Foreground="#A0E0A0">
                <Run FontWeight="Bold">Final note:</Run>
                <Run>
                    Cone Penalties is simple, but it is easy to misunderstand. It is not the cone, and it is not the timer.
                    It is the rule that lets traffic cone hits increase the Count Up timer.
                </Run>
            </TextBlock>
        </Border>
    </BlockUIContainer>

</FlowDocument>